But there *is* a secret code, the [`xmp` tag][1]. It is well supported in browsers, though it will probably never make its way (back) to specifications. Moreover, in addition to rendering all of the contents literally, it is rendered as a block with vertical margins and in monospace font. This can be handled in CSS, with the usual caveats, e.g.

    &lt;style&gt;
